$dateexpire = '001766785127';
$ser_content = 'a:2:{s:7:"CONTENT";s:0:"";s:4:"VARS";a:6:{i:188;a:22:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"188";s:4:"NAME";s:12:"IVF Programs";s:4:"CODE";s:12:"ivf-programs";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2836";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:115:"ART programs (assisted reproductive technologies): IVF, ICSI, frozen embryo transfer and intra-uterine insemination";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:23:"/services/ivf-programs/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"10";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-1";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"1";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:2367:"&lt;p&gt;According to&nbsp;the statistic data, about one couple of&nbsp;seven has to&nbsp;consider IVF as&nbsp;the only way to&nbsp;conceive a&nbsp;child. During the procedure, an&nbsp;egg is&nbsp;fertilized with sperm in&nbsp;the laboratory. Then an&nbsp;embryo is&nbsp;transferred into the woman&rsquo;s uterine cavity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current technologies help to&nbsp;increase success rates in&nbsp;the IVF treatment programs in&nbsp;some cases up&nbsp;to&nbsp;50% and more. Chances are higher in&nbsp;women under 35. In&nbsp;any case, the procedure is&nbsp;safe and can be&nbsp;repeated many times until the wished result is&nbsp;achieved.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;In&nbsp;what cases is&nbsp;IVF indicated?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The procedure is&nbsp;indicated if&nbsp;there is&nbsp;no&nbsp;other way to&nbsp;treat infertility:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;non-patent fallopian tubes due to&nbsp;their pathology;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;no&nbsp;fallopian tubes;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;no&nbsp;ovulation or&nbsp;small number of&nbsp;eggs and their low quality;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;no&nbsp;uterus or&nbsp;ovaries;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;small number of&nbsp;motile or&nbsp;morphologically normal sperm in&nbsp;a&nbsp;male partner;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;confirmed endometriosis;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;sexual disorders that prevent conception.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IVF is&nbsp;also possible in&nbsp;the case of&nbsp;serious hereditary diseases in&nbsp;the history: during the treatment program the embryos will be&nbsp;tested and only healthy embryos will be&nbsp;transferred into the uterine cavity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Where to&nbsp;do&nbsp;IVF in&nbsp;Saint-Petersburg?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IVF is&nbsp;just one infertility treatment program. Our International Centre for Reproductive Medicine (ICRM) practices different methods and technologies: stimulated and natural cycle IVF, ICSI, PGT, assisted hatching and other procedures. The key to&nbsp;success is&nbsp;having full information. Before the treatment program, the doctor will administer a&nbsp;number of&nbsp;tests for both partners. Based on&nbsp;the data received, the specialist will determine what treatment program will fit your needs best to&nbsp;help you conceive and give birth to&nbsp;the baby, and will inform you of&nbsp;the costs of&nbsp;your treatment.&lt;/p&gt;";s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:26:"/upload/iblock/079/eco.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:49:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/079/0_0_1_95/eco.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:26:"/upload/iblock/079/eco.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/079/114_114_1_95/eco.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:26:"/upload/iblock/079/eco.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/079/114_114_1_95/eco.webp";s:8:"category";s:26:"/upload/iblock/079/eco.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/079/114_114_1_95/eco.webp";s:6:"prices";s:26:"/upload/iblock/079/eco.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/079/114_114_1_95/eco.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:0;}i:186;a:22:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"186";s:4:"NAME";s:9:"Donorship";s:4:"CODE";s:23:"donorship-and-surrogacy";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2834";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:53:"IVF with donor eggs or sperm. Our own bank of donors.";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:34:"/services/donorship-and-surrogacy/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"20";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:5:"menu-";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"1";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:3031:"&lt;p&gt;
	ICRM doctors help infertile couples to&nbsp;become parents with the help of&nbsp;egg donation, embryo adoption and surrogacy programs. Our patients can suggest their own candidate to&nbsp;an&nbsp;egg donor and a&nbsp;surrogate mother, or&nbsp;select one from our bank.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Egg donation IVF program&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The program is&nbsp;offered to&nbsp;those patients who do&nbsp;not have their own oocytes (due to&nbsp;premature ovarian failure, removal of&nbsp;the ovaries in&nbsp;the history or&nbsp;menopause), who have too few eggs and for this reason good embryos cannot be&nbsp;made in&nbsp;IVF cycles, or&nbsp;if&nbsp;a&nbsp;woman has a&nbsp;hereditary disease. Here are the stages of&nbsp;the treatment program:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pre-treatment examination and tests for a&nbsp;recipient (a&nbsp;woman who has problems with oocytes) and an&nbsp;egg donor;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;IVF/ICSI treatment program that includes hormonal stimulation of&nbsp;the donor’s ovaries and preparation of&nbsp;the recipient’s endometrium for embryo transfer;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fertilization of&nbsp;the donor’s eggs retrieved at&nbsp;the follicular puncture with the sperm of&nbsp;the recipient’s partner or&nbsp;donor in&nbsp;the laboratory;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;embryo culture;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;embryo transfer to&nbsp;the prepared womb of&nbsp;the recipient;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;post-transfer support with medications;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pregnancy testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	If&nbsp;frozen donor eggs are used, some of&nbsp;the stages are skipped&nbsp;— donor eggs will just be&nbsp;thawed when necessary and fertilized, then the best embryos will be&nbsp;transferred to&nbsp;the recipient’s uterine cavity.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Embryo donation IVF treatment program&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In&nbsp;IVF protocols with the embryos made of&nbsp;donor eggs and donor sperm, both fresh and frozen biological material can be&nbsp;used (but only frozen donor sperm). If&nbsp;fresh oocytes are used, the following stages will be&nbsp;completed before the embryo transfer and pregnancy testing:
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;pre-treatment examination and tests for a&nbsp;recipient and a&nbsp;donor;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;eggs retrieval by&nbsp;means of&nbsp;hormonal stimulation of&nbsp;the donor’s ovaries and her follicle puncture;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;donor eggs fertilization by&nbsp;donor sperm followed by&nbsp;embryo culture;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;preparation of&nbsp;the recipient’s uterine lining.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	In&nbsp;the case of&nbsp;frozen donor eggs, the protocol will be&nbsp;much shorter&nbsp;— it&nbsp;will only be&nbsp;necessary to&nbsp;prepare the endometrium of&nbsp;the future mother, to&nbsp;thaw the embryo when it&nbsp;is&nbsp;necessary and transfer it&nbsp;into her womb. In&nbsp;ICRM, we&nbsp;offer PGT-tested and recommended for transfer embryos for adoption.
&lt;/p&gt;";s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:28:"/upload/iblock/dca/donor.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:51:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/dca/0_0_1_95/donor.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:28:"/upload/iblock/dca/donor.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:55:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/dca/114_114_1_95/donor.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:28:"/upload/iblock/dca/donor.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:55:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/dca/114_114_1_95/donor.webp";s:8:"category";s:28:"/upload/iblock/dca/donor.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:55:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/dca/114_114_1_95/donor.webp";s:6:"prices";s:28:"/upload/iblock/dca/donor.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:55:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/dca/114_114_1_95/donor.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:0;}i:185;a:22:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"185";s:4:"NAME";s:13:"Genetic Tests";s:4:"CODE";s:13:"genetic-tests";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2833";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:113:"Pre-implantation genetic testing (PGT) and screening (PGS) and other genetic and molecular-genetic investigations";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:24:"/services/genetic-tests/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"30";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-9";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:2474:"&lt;h2&gt;Why are genetic tests important for pregnancy?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why is&nbsp;it&nbsp;important for any couple to&nbsp;see a&nbsp;genetic counselor at&nbsp;the stage of&nbsp;family planning? What can be&nbsp;found from genetic tests?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IVF followed by&nbsp;preimplantation genetic testing is&nbsp;performed to&nbsp;select only those embryos that have not inherited a&nbsp;genetic condition.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Genetic testing within an&nbsp;IVF treatment program can help to&nbsp;find a&nbsp;healthy embryo and transfer it&nbsp;into the uterus. This will make the chances for successful pregnancy higher. There are two types of&nbsp;preimplantation genetic testing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;genetic diagnosis (PGD);&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;genetic screening (PGS).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is&nbsp;the purpose of&nbsp;genetic tests within an&nbsp;IVF program?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGD is&nbsp;required when both parents have a&nbsp;gene mutation or&nbsp;a&nbsp;chromosomal rearrangement. In&nbsp;such cases, there is&nbsp;a&nbsp;high risk of&nbsp;a&nbsp;genetic condition in&nbsp;a&nbsp;future baby. Genetic diagnosis can help to&nbsp;reveal and exclude it&nbsp;in&nbsp;an&nbsp;embryo. The embryos that did not pass the diagnostic procedure are not transferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To&nbsp;select an&nbsp;embryo, genetic screening is&nbsp;not required. The procedure is&nbsp;recommended in&nbsp;the following cases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;severe male infertility;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;miscarriages in&nbsp;the history;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;IVF failures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PGS is&nbsp;possible to&nbsp;do&nbsp;in&nbsp;the case parents want&nbsp;to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;find out the sex of&nbsp;a&nbsp;future child;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;exclude late-onset diseases like Alzheimer&rsquo;s;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;exclude non-life threatening diseases;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;find out about genetic predispositions in&nbsp;a&nbsp;future baby.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The essence of&nbsp;every method of&nbsp;genetic screening is&nbsp;investigation of&nbsp;cell chromosomal structure and functions performed at&nbsp;any stage of&nbsp;their life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our genetic counselor provides consultations to&nbsp;the patients planning a&nbsp;family, and refers to&nbsp;necessary genetic tests to&nbsp;make sure you have a&nbsp;healthy child.&lt;/p&gt;";s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:30:"/upload/iblock/746/genetic.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/746/0_0_1_95/genetic.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:30:"/upload/iblock/746/genetic.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/746/114_114_1_95/genetic.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:30:"/upload/iblock/746/genetic.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/746/114_114_1_95/genetic.webp";s:8:"category";s:30:"/upload/iblock/746/genetic.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/746/114_114_1_95/genetic.webp";s:6:"prices";s:30:"/upload/iblock/746/genetic.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/746/114_114_1_95/genetic.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:0;}i:183;a:22:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"183";s:4:"NAME";s:20:"Reproductive Surgery";s:4:"CODE";s:20:"reproductive-surgery";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2831";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:103:"Diagnostic and treatment procedures such as biopsy, laparoscopy, hysteroscopy, urologic surgery, etc.  ";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:31:"/services/reproductive-surgery/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"70";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-4";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"1";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";N;s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:30:"/upload/iblock/393/surgery.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/393/0_0_1_95/surgery.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:30:"/upload/iblock/393/surgery.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/393/114_114_1_95/surgery.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:30:"/upload/iblock/393/surgery.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/393/114_114_1_95/surgery.webp";s:8:"category";s:30:"/upload/iblock/393/surgery.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/393/114_114_1_95/surgery.webp";s:6:"prices";s:30:"/upload/iblock/393/surgery.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:57:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/393/114_114_1_95/surgery.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:1;}i:182;a:22:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"182";s:4:"NAME";s:19:"In-Patient Services";s:4:"CODE";s:19:"in-patient-services";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2830";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:90:"Using our in-patient facilities to rest after surgical interventions and ovarian punctures";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:30:"/services/in-patient-services/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"80";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-7";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";N;s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";N;s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:31:"/upload/iblock/c6f/hospital.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:54:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c6f/0_0_1_95/hospital.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:31:"/upload/iblock/c6f/hospital.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:58:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c6f/114_114_1_95/hospital.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:31:"/upload/iblock/c6f/hospital.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:58:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c6f/114_114_1_95/hospital.webp";s:8:"category";s:31:"/upload/iblock/c6f/hospital.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:58:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c6f/114_114_1_95/hospital.webp";s:6:"prices";s:31:"/upload/iblock/c6f/hospital.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:58:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/c6f/114_114_1_95/hospital.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:0;}i:181;a:22:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"181";s:4:"NAME";s:23:"Ultrasound Examinations";s:4:"CODE";s:23:"ultrasound-examinations";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2829";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:16:"Ultrasound scans";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:34:"/services/ultrasound-examinations/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"90";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-3";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"1";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:2364:"&lt;h2&gt;Why do&nbsp;we&nbsp;do&nbsp;ultrasound scans in&nbsp;ICRM?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ultrasound examination is&nbsp;a&nbsp;non-invasive method aimed to&nbsp;assess the condition of&nbsp;internal organs and systems of&nbsp;organs. The main advantages of&nbsp;ultrasound are its safety and high informative value. Based on&nbsp;ultrasound findings, our specialists can:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;verify a&nbsp;diagnosis;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;reveal hidden pathology in&nbsp;asymptomatic patients;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;clarify the cause of&nbsp;infertility;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;evaluate health condition of&nbsp;future mother and father before planning an&nbsp;IVF program, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;During family planning and pregnancy, ultrasound is&nbsp;used to&nbsp;monitor ovulation, to&nbsp;find out the date of&nbsp;conception and pregnancy term, to&nbsp;follow the fetus development, to&nbsp;reveal intrauterine defects, and at&nbsp;the late pregnancy period&nbsp;&mdash; to&nbsp;see the baby&rsquo;s position for better management of&nbsp;labor.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Advantages of&nbsp;ultrasound examination method&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pros of&nbsp;ultrasound screening:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;performed in&nbsp;real-time mode;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;an&nbsp;area to&nbsp;be&nbsp;examined can easily be&nbsp;changed;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;the plan of&nbsp;monitoring can be&nbsp;corrected depending on&nbsp;the current situation;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;image magnification and detailed study of&nbsp;zones of&nbsp;special interest are&nbsp;possible when necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In&nbsp;our International Centre for reproductive Medicine, the following ultrasound examinations are available:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;pelvic ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;breast ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;scrotal ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;kidneys and urinary bladder ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;prostate ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;abdominal ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;thyroid ultrasound;&lt;/li&gt;
   &lt;li&gt;soft tissues ultrasound.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In&nbsp;addition, we&nbsp;offer ultrasound monitoring of&nbsp;ovulation. For pelvic ultrasound both abdominal and vaginal transducers are used.&lt;/p&gt;";s:7:"picture";a:10:{s:8:"ORIGINAL";s:26:"/upload/iblock/0cc/uzi.png";s:13:"webp_ORIGINAL";s:49:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/0cc/0_0_1_95/uzi.webp";s:12:"main_complex";s:26:"/upload/iblock/0cc/uzi.png";s:17:"webp_main_complex";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/0cc/114_114_1_95/uzi.webp";s:14:"services_index";s:26:"/upload/iblock/0cc/uzi.png";s:19:"webp_services_index";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/0cc/114_114_1_95/uzi.webp";s:8:"category";s:26:"/upload/iblock/0cc/uzi.png";s:13:"webp_category";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/0cc/114_114_1_95/uzi.webp";s:6:"prices";s:26:"/upload/iblock/0cc/uzi.png";s:11:"webp_prices";s:53:"/upload/resize_cache/iblock/0cc/114_114_1_95/uzi.webp";}s:24:"showServiceTypesOnPrices";b:0;}}}';
